The paper deals with Named Entity Recognition (NER) using neural network-based models, which is a common topic in the Natural Language Processing (NLP) community. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method for sharing network parameters between two languages, which is related to transfer learning and multi-task learning, both of which are common topics in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses character-level representations, which is a common technique in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible sub-category.
